[156.276279, "o", "\r\n"]
[156.718756, "o", "  {\r\n      \"total_contributions\": 10,\r\n      \"eval_count\": 4,\r\n      \"attack_map_count\": 3,\r\n      \"ioc_bundle_count\": 3,\r\n      \"unique_vendors\": 3,\r\n      \"unique_techniques\": 5,\r\n      \"merkle_root\": \"91e0e961001af53ca859ca6478cf47cec84cf1e4fd12b81e5a46678cb6be0867\",\r\n      \"pending_categories\": 0,\r\n      \"revealed_categories\": 0\r\n  }\r\n"]
[157.729287, "o", "\r\n  Every contribution is committed to a Merkle tree.\r\n"]
[158.539097, "o", "\r\n  The Merkle root is a fingerprint of ALL contributions.\r\n"]
[159.347241, "o", "\r\n  Change one value and the root changes — tamper-evident.\r\n"]
[164.162453, "o", "\r\n  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n"]
[165.169791, "o", "\r\n  Verify the CrowdStrike aggregate is real:\r\n"]
[165.980652, "o", "\r\n  $ curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8799/verify/aggregate/CrowdStrike\r\n"]
[166.099839, "o", "  Contributors: 2\r\n  Merkle root:  91e0e961001af53ca859ca6478cf47cec84cf1e4...\r\n  Valid:         True\r\n    commitment_count_matches: PASS\r\n    merkle_root_present: PASS\r\n    signature_present: PASS\r\n"]
[166.101467, "o", "\r\n  Three checks, all PASS. The aggregate is mathematically\r\n"]
[166.909991, "o", "\r\n  proven to be computed from real committed contributions.\r\n"]
[167.726246, "o", "\r\n  The server can't inflate the count, alter scores, or\r\n"]
[168.543586, "o", "\r\n  exclude contributions. Math, not promises.\r\n"]
[174.376238, "o", "\r\n  ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\r\n"]
[174.376794, "o", "  ║  Plot twist: a new threat actor emerges\r\n  ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\r\n\r\n"]
[176.382509, "o", "\r\n  Three hospitals independently encounter a new ransomware\r\n"]
[177.191206, "o", "\r\n  group called 'DarkAngel' — but it's not in any public\r\n"]
[178.002123, "o", "\r\n  database yet. How do they surface it collectively without\r\n"]
[178.816478, "o", "\r\n  any of them revealing they were attacked?\r\n"]
[179.632716, "o", "\r\n\r\n  Blind category discovery.\r\n"]
[183.695811, "o", "\r\n  Each hospital hashes the name locally:\r\n"]
[184.503672, "o", "    H = SHA-256(\"DarkAngel\":salt) = 5b67724cd0f0a103ae7129beed5019e2...\r\n"]
[185.015071, "o", "    The server will see this hash. Never the name.\r\n"]
[188.53335, "o", "\r\n"]
[188.533423, "o", "  $ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8799/category/propose ... (hospital-a)\r\n"]
[188.664228, "o", "  hospital-a: pending (1/3)\r\n"]
[189.673846, "o", "  $ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8799/category/propose ... (hospital-b)\r\n"]
[189.827105, "o", "  hospital-b: pending (2/3)\r\n"]
[190.832428, "o", "  $ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8799/category/propose ... (hospital-c)\r\n"]
[190.999143, "o", "  hospital-c: threshold_met (3/3)\r\n"]
[192.00881, "o", "\r\n  Three hospitals submitted the same hash independently.\r\n"]
[192.81671, "o", "\r\n  Threshold met. Now they vote to reveal the name:\r\n"]
[196.642181, "o", "\r\n"]
[196.768847, "o", "  hospital-a: vote_recorded \r\n"]
[198.246037, "o", "  hospital-b: revealed darkangel\r\n"]
[199.257491, "o", "\r\n  'DarkAngel' is now a public category. The collective\r\n"]
[200.068606, "o", "\r\n  can aggregate data about it. The server learned the name\r\n"]
[200.882273, "o", "\r\n  only because 3 hospitals independently confirmed it —\r\n"]
[201.694251, "o", "\r\n  and 2 voted to make it public.\r\n"]
[207.51075, "o", "\r\n  ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\r\n  ║  What each side knows\r\n  ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\r\n\r\n"]
[209.529289, "o", "  THE SERVER HAS:                THE SERVER CANNOT SEE:\r\n  ─────────────────              ──────────────────────\r\n  Commitment hashes (SHA-256)    Individual scores\r\n"]
[209.529569, "o", "  Running sums per vendor        Which hospital submitted what\r\n  Technique frequency counters   Free-text notes or sigma rules\r\n  Merkle tree                    Raw IOC values (IPs, domains)\r\n  Blind category hashes          Who proposed which category\r\n\r\n"]
[213.542315, "o", "\r\n  Without nur: each hospital fights alone, misses the\r\n"]
[214.35185, "o", "\r\n  campaign connection, buys tools based on vendor marketing.\r\n"]
[215.160963, "o", "\r\n"]
[215.161162, "o", "\r\n  With nur: collaborative defense with mathematical\r\n"]
[215.974993, "o", "\r\n  privacy guarantees. 575 tests. Zero individual values.\r\n"]
[216.785916, "o", "\r\n"]
[219.792527, "o", "  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\r\n  │                                                             │\r\n"]
[219.792622, "o", "  │   Attackers share everything.                               │\r\n  │   Defenders share nothing.                                  │\r\n  │   nur fixes that.                                           │\r\n  │                                                             │\r\n  │   nur.saramena.us · github.com/manizzle/nur                │\r\n  │                                                             │\r\n  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\r\n\r\n"]
